CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 31, 1946, pg. 8 reads: "Till Death Do Us Part" - The Rev. B.S.Mason officiated at the recent marriage of Miss Virginia Moore, daughter of Mr.and Mrs. Coleman Shelton, and Cleo Wesley, son of the Rev. and Mrs. T.D. Wesley. The young couple was married at the home of Mr. and Mrs. Wesley Irons.  in wedding party were Miss Edith Brow, maid of honor; John Saunders, best man; the bride and groom; usher John Farris, and bridesmaid Mrs. Mary Moore. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of five men, seven women, boy, and girl, including groom Cleo Wesley, bride Virginia Moore wearing gown with sheer panels on shoulders, and bridesmaid Mary Moore, posed in interior
